Usage: SHOWIDLE [[-N|-O] [-SN|SO] channels [filter]]
  Shows idle time for users on channel

  Shows idle time for specified channel. If no channel is given current
  channel is used. If filter is given, idle time for users matching filter
  is displayed. To display only channel operators specify -O. To display
  non operators use -N. Output can be sorted, use -SN to display least
  idle users first and use -SO to display most idle users first.

See also:
  IDLEKICK
  IDLETIME
